Office of Global Engagement     Search the site     Toggle Menu      Search                  Office of Global Engagement      Office of Global Engagement   Google Translate        Main Menu    OIA           Office of International Affairs         OIS           Office of International Services         PIP           Programs for International Partnerships         SAO           Study Abroad Office         TIE           Tutorium in Intensive English         UIC Global     Eyebrow menu    International Admissions    International Centers and Programs    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                     Participants of the Summer Study Abroad Program Gather at the Residence of Consul General of France    Posted on January 17, 2020                            On January 17th, at the Residence of Consul General of France, M. Guillaume Lacroix, participants of the summer study abroad program organized and lead by Prof. Kathryn Engel—Director of Internships of Applied Psychology, Senior Lecturer in the Department of Psychology, and Faculty Fellow of the Honors College—gathered to be congratulated for their hard work and dedication during the summer 2019 program abroad. This program takes UIC undergraduates to a summer full time internship in the city of Paris' social services offices. Students are assigned to projects with local mentors under the supervision of Prof. Engel. In the photo from left to right are: Mary-Benedict Obikili, Andrew Ha, Mme. Lacroix, Prof. Engel, Consul General Lacroix, Katherine Reyes, Jacob Krol, and Abigail Suleman.      Modified on March 02, 2020
